<subSubSection id="C33EC4D1754AD70E82C5F62F5BCBF5C6" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9B975A754AD70E82C5F62F5ABEF5B9" blockId="5.[2015,2611,2496,2920]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="B9504B48754AD70E82C5F62F5A05F660" bold="true" box="[2015,2171,2496,2525]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C24ECD9754AD70E8D93F62F5854F660" authority="De Beaux, 1923" authorityName="De Beaux" authorityYear="1923" box="[2185,2602,2496,2525]" class="Mammalia" family="Nycteridae" genus="Petalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parisii">Petalia parisii De Beaux, 1923</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B4C9D07754AD70E82FBF6085ABEF5B9" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3804723305" box="[2017,2240,2535,2564]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">
“Balli, 
<collectingCountry id="F333D7CA754AD70E8D27F6085ACCF5B9" box="[2109,2226,2535,2564]" name="Somalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Somalia</collectingCountry>
.”
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B975A754AD70E82FAF5E45BCBF5C6" blockId="5.[2015,2611,2496,2920]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicName id="4C24ECD9754AD70E82FAF5E45AD3F591" authorityName="E. Geoffroy &amp; G. Cuvier" authorityYear="1795" box="[2016,2221,2571,2604]" class="Mammalia" family="Nycteridae" genus="Nycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="paris">Nycteris paris</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C24ECD9754AD70E8CD6F5E4584DF591" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1876" box="[2508,2611,2571,2604]" class="Mammalia" family="Nycteridae" genus="Nycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotis">macrotis</taxonomicName>
group. It was previously considered conspecific with N. wood:i. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33EC4D1754AD70E82C5F56E5A4CF54C" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" type="distribution">
<caption id="DF5BC7D2754AD70E82C5F56E5A4CF54C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6576972" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6576972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6576972/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" targetBox="[1399,1992,2498,2913]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8B9B975A754AD70E82C5F56E5A4CF54C" blockId="5.[2015,2611,2496,2920]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="B9504B48754AD70E82C5F56E5AEEF51F" bold="true" box="[2015,2192,2689,2722]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from just four localities in N 
<collectingCountry id="F333D7CA754AD70E8D7AF55D5A86F576" box="[2144,2296,2738,2763]" name="Cameroon" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, S 
<collectingCountry id="F333D7CA754AD70E8C39F55D5BE3F576" box="[2339,2461,2738,2763]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, and S 
<collectingCountry id="F333D7CA754AD70E8F1DF55D5A50F54C" name="Somalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Somalia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33EC4D1754AD70E82C5F5175B2BF460" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9B975A754AD70E82C5F5175B2BF460" blockId="5.[2015,2611,2496,2920]" lastBlockId="5.[1399,2608,2926,3471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="B9504B48754AD70E82C5F5175AA4F4A4" bold="true" box="[2015,2266,2808,2841]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 46-47 mm, tail 44-50 mm, ear 
<quantity id="4CDC3ABF754AD70E8C3DF4C75BE9F4FC" box="[2343,2455,2856,2881]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
, hindfoot 
<quantity id="4CDC3ABF754AD70E82C5F4A05A4FF4D5" box="[2015,2097,2895,2920]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
, forearm 38-41 mm; weight 
<quantity id="4CDC3ABF754AD70E8CD9F4A05B93F4D5" box="[2499,2541,2895,2920]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" unit="g" value="7.0">7 g</quantity>
. Parisi’s Slit-faced Batis very small and has short, rounded wings. Longitudinal cleft runs along top of muzzle, covering noseleaves. Furis long and fluffy, grayish brown dorsally, and grayish ventrally. Ears are long. Wing membranes are dark brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33EC4D1754AD70E8063F40C5AF3F3B9" box="[1401,2189,3043,3076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B9B975A754AD70E8063F40C5AF3F3B9" blockId="5.[1399,2608,2926,3471]" box="[1401,2189,3043,3076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="B9504B48754AD70E8063F40C5797F3B9" bold="true" box="[1401,1513,3043,3076]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Habitat.</emphasis>
Riverine forests or swamps in semiarid savanna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
