<subSubSection id="C33EC4D1754AD70E8063F3465B46F2FD" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8B9B975A754AD70E8063F3465B46F2FD" blockId="5.[1399,2608,2926,3471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="B9504B48754AD70E8063F34654A2F377" bold="true" box="[1401,1756,3241,3274]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Justfive specimens of Parisi’s Slit-faced Bat have been collected at four widely different geographical locations. Until more information becomes available, Parisi’s Slit-faced Bat will remain one of the poorest known bats on the African continent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
